RACE.RACE_TEXT: SUFFOLK DOWNS RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 9200. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of a race since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. A race since May 23 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHELLY'S CIDER dueled outside, drew off in the upper stretch and was kept to late light urging. DOUBLE THE SILK was outrun early, saved ground advancing into the stretch, angled out and had a mild rally. PRETTY NELL dueled inside to the stretch and weakened. RED RED DOOR raced in the second flight, bore out into the stretch and had no rally. AULT STREET trailed and passed tiring rivals. FAIR CHASE was outrun three-wide early and fanned six-wide into the stretch. ARA BEST rushed to press the early pace, bore out tiring on the turn, fanned eight-wide and was eased.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SUFFOLK DOWNS RACE 2 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 9000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JANUARY 23. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MIMITO BOY ducked in squeezing AMBRAW at the start, quickly took command, set a lively pace into the stretch and was put to strong urging. DANCE TO THE ROAR ducked out squeezing AMBRAW at the start, was well placed, proved no match but was up for the place. THIS ONES FOR NINA went three- to four-wide on the first turn, remained three-wide on the second turn and lacked a rally. U S S CONSTITUTION lagged for five furlongs and finished well.. AMBRAW was squeezed back at the start and no threat. I CAN AND I WILL was outrun and fanned four-wide. FOUR F'S AND A D pressed the pace three- to four-wide on the first turn, remained well placed to the second turn and then gave way.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SUFFOLK DOWNS RACE 3 5F Turf CR: 91. Claiming Purse 13000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners of two races since June 23 Allowed 2 lbs. A race since May 23 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000 (Races where entered for $6,250 or less not considered in estimating allowances). (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race on the Turf, it will be run on the main track at Five Furlongs.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: EVERYDAY DAVE dueled inside into the stretch and drew off under intermittent urging. E. J. LITTLE BOY was outrun early and saved ground rallying into the turn. COPELAN'S RIDGE stalked the pace, went three-wide into the stretch and lacked the needed late response. LIBERTY ST. OUTLAW was outrun into the stretch and no factor. MY VALENTINO dueled outside to the quarter pole where he took a bad step, lugged in, took another bad step and drifted right in the final sixteenth. THE STEWARDS SAID THE TRACK VETERINARIAN SAID MY VALENTINO WAS SUFFERING FROM THE HEAT AND WAS VANNED OFF. HENGROEN was outrun and saved ground to no avail. KHAN OF KHANS was well placed to the stretch and tired. MR. B. W. trailed into the turn, tried to advance along the rail, was taken up and was through. HOOKED ON GLORY raced in the middle of the pack and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: SUFFOLK DOWNS RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 42. Maiden Claiming Purse 9000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DAKOTA'S PICK pressed the pace into the stretch, lugged in, straightened and drew off, lugged in again seventy yards out and prevailed under strong urging. THATWOULDBEALL sprinted clear and responded gamely when challenged. SPECTACULAR SILK raced in the middle of the pack and had no rally. GO MARELIN GO dueled inside for three furlongs and tired. JAZZY GINGER BELLE pressed the pace briefly and tired. THE DARK LION trailed. AFTER THE RIDER OF THATWOULDBEALL CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF DAKOTA'S PICK, ALLEGING INTERFERENCE IN THE FINAL SIXTEENTH, AND THE RIDER OF JAZZY GINGER BELLE CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF DAKOTA'S PICK, ALLEGING INTEFERENCE NEAR THE HALF-MILE POLE, THE STEWARDS REVIEWED THE RUNNING AND ALLOWED THE RESULT TO STAND.
